<li class="jqslider">
 <div class="home-banner-main">
 <h2>The Cross+Word Archive</h2>
 <p>You have probably reached this front page as a result of an old link. Or perhaps you came in seach of the Banner Ministries website that has been on the internet since the mid-1990's. No matter how you arrived here, you are very welcome to browse the articles, even though most of them are showing their age. If this is entirely new to you, take a look at the website and ministry information, and select from the article categories.</p>
 </div><!-- end home-banner-main -->

 <div class="home-banner-sub">
 <div class="home-banner-sub-content">
 <a href=""><img src="images/boxes.jpg" alt="Former Cross+Word Graphic" width="436" height="270" /></a>
 </div><!-- end home-banner-sub-content -->
 </div><!-- end home-banner-sub --></li>

<li class="jqslider">
 <div class="home-banner-main">
 <h2>The Church Under Attack</h2>
 <p>The past few decades have brought immense and confusing changes to the Church. We are tossed on a sea of contradictory teachings. Finding out what's false and what's real is not easy but this website seeks to help, with explanatory articles and comparisons from scripture.</p>
 </div><!-- end home-banner-main -->

 <div class="home-banner-sub">
 <div class="home-banner-sub-content">
 <a href=""><img src="images/green_storm.jpg" alt="Storm at Sea" width="436" height="270" /></a>
 </div><!-- end home-banner-sub-content -->
 </div><!-- end home-banner-sub --></li> 
 
 <li class="jqslider">
 <div class="home-banner-main">
 <h2>From Where Is Our Peace?</h2>
 <p>We feel hurried and stressed, and have little time for the Lord. Yet our peace comes from spending time with Him! However dark the pathway, there is a place of rest in God. The path only becomes clear once we commit to God's leading and guidance.</p>
 </div><!-- end home-banner-main -->

